    <item>
      <title>Smallest Todo List</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/journal/2024/articles/smallest-todo-list/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 17 May 2023 17:10:24 +0100</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/journal/2024/articles/smallest-todo-list/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Make it smaller than that.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;No, even smaller.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;It doesn&amp;rsquo;t matter what method you use, software or notebook, audio message or knot in your handkerchief.&#xA;What&amp;rsquo;s important is the item itself.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;For me it has to be small.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;tiny.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;As someone with a lifetime award for procrastination, if I feel resistance to doing a task I will do something else.&#xA;Anything else.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;One of the best ways to make a task palatable is to make it smaller.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Aw Yiss, Breadcrumbs</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/journal/2024/articles/aw-yiss-breadcrumbs/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 20 Mar 2023 13:37:23 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/journal/2024/articles/aw-yiss-breadcrumbs/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;I think I&amp;rsquo;m going to be talking about procrastination quite often.&#xA;It&amp;rsquo;s been the bane of my life for a long time now.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;If I&amp;rsquo;m going to leave things unfinished or interrupt myself I need to &lt;strong&gt;find a way to restart&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;m trying to leave a &lt;strong&gt;trail of breadcrumbs&lt;/strong&gt; that can get me back on track.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;These make it easier to recover from getting sidetracked.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;&#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;  &lt;figure class=&#34;mx-auto my-0 rounded-md&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;      &#xA;      &#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;  &#xA;    &lt;picture&#xA;      class=&#34;mx-auto my-0 rounded-md&#34;&#xA;      &#xA;    &gt;&#xA;      &#xA;      &#xA;      &#xA;      &#xA;        &lt;source&#xA;          &#xA;            srcset=&#34;http://localhost:1313/journal/2024/articles/aw-yiss-breadcrumbs/awyiss_hu6556425445387626773.webp 330w,/journal/2024/articles/aw-yiss-breadcrumbs/awyiss_hu14462157050557890194.webp 660w&#xA; &#xA; &#xA; ,/journal/2024/articles/aw-yiss-breadcrumbs/awyiss_hu3062376222763388013.webp 696w&#xA; &#xA; &#xA; &#xA; &#xA; ,/journal/2024/articles/aw-yiss-breadcrumbs/awyiss_hu3062376222763388013.webp 696w&#xA; &#xA; &#34;&#xA;          &#xA;          sizes=&#34;100vw&#34;&#xA;          type=&#34;image/webp&#34;&#xA;        /&gt;&#xA;      &#xA;      &lt;img&#xA;        width=&#34;696&#34;&#xA;        height=&#34;303&#34;&#xA;        class=&#34;mx-auto my-0 rounded-md&#34;&#xA;        alt=&#34;Aw Yiss, a duck finds some breadcrumbs&#34;&#xA;        loading=&#34;lazy&#34; decoding=&#34;async&#34;&#xA;        &#xA;          src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/journal/2024/articles/aw-yiss-breadcrumbs/awyiss_hu8924567888517062038.png&#34;&#xA;          srcset=&#34;http://localhost:1313/journal/2024/articles/aw-yiss-breadcrumbs/awyiss_hu2881182838645585289.png 330w,/journal/2024/articles/aw-yiss-breadcrumbs/awyiss_hu8924567888517062038.png 660w&#xA; &#xA; ,/journal/2024/articles/aw-yiss-breadcrumbs/awyiss.png 696w&#xA; &#xA; &#xA; ,/journal/2024/articles/aw-yiss-breadcrumbs/awyiss.png 696w&#xA; &#34;&#xA;          sizes=&#34;100vw&#34;&#xA;        &#xA;      /&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/picture&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;figcaption class=&#34;text-center&#34;&gt;by &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.harkavagrant.com/index.php&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noreferrer&#34;&gt;Kate Beaton&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.harkavagrant.com/nonsense/gorey5.png&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noreferrer&#34;&gt;Hark! A Vagrant&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/figcaption&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;!-- OR &#xA;![Abstract purple artwork](awyiss.png &#34;Photo by [Jr Korpa](https://unsplash.com/@jrkorpa) on [Unsplash](https://unsplash.com/)&#34;)&#xA;--&gt;&#xA;&lt;h4 id=&#34;breadcrumbs&#34; class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Breadcrumbs &lt;span class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700&#34; style=&#34;text-decoration-line: none !important;&#34; href=&#34;#breadcrumbs&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;I have a &lt;a href=&#34;https://nesslabs.com/gratitude&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noreferrer&#34;&gt;gratitude journal&lt;/a&gt; listing things I&amp;rsquo;ve done and things I&amp;rsquo;m grateful for every day.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I am very self critical and filling this in has helped me develop the habit of thinking about the positives.&#xA;I leave the journal next to my bed and write just before I sleep, which helps avoid ruminating and keeping me awake.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
